title: Crude suicide rate in Vietnam 2000 to 2015
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Crude suicide rate per 100,000 inhabitants. In total the number of data points it has is 4.
Overall Crude suicide rate per 100,000 inhabitants has increased over the Year.
Crude suicide rate per 100,000 inhabitants is slightly increasing from 2000 to 2015.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2005 and 2010.
Maximum Crude suicide rate per 100,000 inhabitants, about 7.4 was reported at Year 2015
The lowest Crude suicide rate per 100,000 inhabitants, of value 6.5 was reported at Year 2005
